urugamer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@linuxgurugamer\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0is one of the best mod creators, so i am\u00A0sure it works the way\u00A0you want \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E .\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d like to turn them off in the tracking station.\u00A0 This doesn\u0027t let you do that.\u00A0 This is for when you\u0027re physically in orbit with your ship.\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223664651\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187891\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221567307912\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022128005\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022OhioBob\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 hours ago, OhioBob said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/89401-jpinard/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002289401\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/89401-jpinard/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@jpinard\u003C/a\u003E, install \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/181547-173-1-backports-kopernicus-kittopiatech/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EKopernicus\u003C/a\u003E and try this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E@Kopernicus:FINAL\n{\n\t@Body,*\n\t{\n\t\t@Orbit\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tmode = OFF\n\t\t\ticon = NONE\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003Emode\u003C/strong\u003E draws the orbit line and \u003Cstrong\u003Eicon\u003C/strong\u003E is the dot showing the planet position.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNeat!\u00A0 Will give that a try.\u00A0 Thanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-02T13:26:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223665219\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187891\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221567381343\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289401\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jpinard\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, jpinard said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d like to turn them off in the tracking station.\u00A0 This doesn\u0027t let you do that.\u00A0 This is for when you\u0027re physically in orbit with your ship.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo you want to turn them off in the Map view?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jpinard","CreatedById":89401,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-02T16:02:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223665557\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187891\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221567430800\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo you want to turn them off in the Map view?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom the tracking station - yep \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OhioBob","CreatedById":128005,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-02T16:15:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe config I gave, assuming I did it right, should turn them off everywhere, including the map view and tracking station.\u00A0 Turning them off, however, means you can\u0027t click on and target the planet.\u00A0 As I recall, I think you just need the icon to target a planet.\u00A0 So you could try turning off the orbits lines (mode = OFF) and keeping the icon as is.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-02T17:38:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223665659\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187891\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221567440179\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289401\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jpinard\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, jpinard said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom the tracking station - yep \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)